Description: An encoding where each digit of a code is either on or off (we say it has a binary state, usually represented with 0s and 1s).
Description (Chinese): 一种编码方式，其中代码的每个位要么是开要么是关（通常表示为0或1）。

Description: Short for binary digit: the digits in a binary system.
Description (Chinese): 二进制系统中的单个数字，简称二进制位。
元胞自动机。指基于简单规则模拟复杂行为的系统。*
也称为分数布朗运动，是标准布朗运动的扩展，由Mandelbrot和Van Ness于1968年提出，是一种描述自然界中不规则形状和长程相关性的随机过程。*

Spanish: Mapa de Ruido de Densidad Fraccional

Description: A code where each digit of the code has 16 possible states (usually represented as 0 to 9 and then A to F). It's most commonly implemented with signal strength values, where ss 0 represents 0, ss10 represents A, ss15 represents F and so on. Multiple hex signals can be combined to form a code with multiple digits. For example, valid three digit hex codes are 032, AFF, 0F4.
Description (Chinese): 在数学中是一种逢16进1的进位制。一般用数字0到9和字母A到F表示，其中：A~F相当于十进制的10~15，这些称作十六进制数字。
